:::summary
Rhetoric — the art of persuasion through language — is one of the three foundational disciplines of the classical liberal arts (the *trivium*: grammar, logic, and rhetoric) and has been studied, practiced, and taught since ancient Greece. From Aristotle's systematic analysis to Cicero's magnificent Latin orations to the sermons of Augustine and the preaching of every faithful minister since, rhetoric is the art of using words well in service of truth — an indispensable skill for anyone who wishes to teach, lead, preach, or persuade.
